<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES FS-5106 AND FS-6206 - REASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT AND REVERSE IDLER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="8">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT AND REVERSE IDLER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press 3rd gear on the countershaft as shown, splined end of gear hub to the front of the
                shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300874">Figure 74</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300874" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300874" filename="../figg13/G1300872.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Press 3rd Gear on Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press 4th speed gear on the countershaft, long hub of the gear to the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300875">Figure 75</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300875" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300875" filename="../figg13/G1300875.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 75. Press 4th Gear on Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 5th and 6th speed gear keys on the countershaft (inset,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300876">Figure 76</hotlnk>). Align the keyway of 5th speed gear to the key on the
                shaft. Press 5th gear on, long hub of gear to front of the shaft.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300876" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300876" filename="../figg13/G1300876.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Install 5th and 6th Speed Gear Keys and Align Keyway of 5th Speed Gear to Key
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align keyway of drive gear to the key on the countershaft. Press drive gear on, long hub of
                gear to the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300877">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300877" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300877" filename="../figg13/G1300877.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Align Keyway of Drive Gear to Key on Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install snap ring in the groove at the front of the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300878">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300878" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300878" filename="../figg13/G1300878.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Install Snap Ring in Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the front countershaft bearing as shown (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300879">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300879" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300879" filename="../figg13/G1300879.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Install Front Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rear countershaft bearing as shown (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300880">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300880" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300880" filename="../figg13/G1300880.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Install Rear Countershaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the snap ring, countershaft front bearing race (from inside
                of case) and bore plug (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300881">Figure 81</hotlnk>). Coat outer diameter of the bore plug with Loctite #510
                before installing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300881" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300881" filename="../figg13/G1300881.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Install Snap Ring, Countershaft Front Bearing Race and Bore Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
